Title: Putting photos in order
Description: Choose which of the two photos is more complex
Answer.criteria: Mostly I looked at how many different things were going on in the picture. I also looked at how the picture joined together. If it was one coherent image I felt that was more complex than if it was jumbled together. Just adding more things to the image didn't necessarily make it more complex. But adding more things in a coherent way to make it seem like one large image tended to make ti seem more complex.

Title: Putting photos in order
Description: Choose which of the two photos is more complex
Answer.criteria: One factor of complexity was how much of the space in the picture was filled up.  If there were only a few lines or items shown, then I would say the photo was simple. However, if there were multiple lines and items, then I would classify the photo as complex.  Also, another factor was color. If there were a variety of colors shown, then I think the photo was complex. Finally, another aspect of complexity, was the number and variety of items shown.  The more variety, and number of items depicted, the more complex I'd classify the photo shown.
Answer.feedbackForStudy: I think it was an interesting study.
